{"title_page": "Tom Spence", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2017}}\n{{infobox football biography\n| name = Tom Spence\n\n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date|1962|01|04|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Airdrie, North Lanarkshire|Airdrie]], Scotland\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2012|04|28|1962|01|04|df=y}}\n| height = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Left-back]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = Glenboig\n| years1 = 1982\u20131988 | caps1 = 147 | goals1 = 6  | clubs1 = [[Stirling Albion F.C.|Stirling Albion]]\n| years2 = 1988      | caps2 = 1   | goals2 = 0  | clubs2 = [[Alloa Athletic F.C.|Alloa Athletic]]\n| years3 = 1988      | caps3 = 2   | goals3 = 0  | clubs3 = [[Cowdenbeath F.C.|Cowdenbeath]]\n| years4 = 1988\u20131989 | caps4 = 29  | goals4 = 4  | clubs4 = [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]]\n| years5 = 1989\u20131990 | caps5 = 12  | goals5 = 0  | clubs5 = [[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]]\n| years6 = 1990\u20131991 | caps6 = 50  | goals6 = 1  | clubs6 = [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]\n| years7 = 1991\u20131993 | caps7 = 58  | goals7 = 1  | clubs7 = [[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]]\n| years8 = 1993\u20131994 | caps8 = 12  | goals8 = 0  | clubs8 = [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]]\n| totalcaps = 311\n| totalgoals = 12\n| manageryears1 = 1994\u20131995\n| managerclubs1 = [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]]\n}}\n\n'''Tom Spence''' (4 January 1962 \u2013 28 April 2012) was a Scottish [[association football|football]] player and [[manager (association football)|manager]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cumnockjuniorsfc.co.uk/2012/04/tom-spence/ |title=Tom Spence |publisher=Cumnock Juniors FC |date=2012-04-25 |accessdate=2012-04-29}} {{dead link|date=July 2015}}</ref> He was born in [[Airdrie, North Lanarkshire]]. Spence played for [[Stirling Albion F.C.|Stirling Albion]], [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]], [[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]] and [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] and was captain of the Stirling Albion team which defeated [[Selkirk F.C.|Selkirk]] 20\u20130 in 1984.<ref>http://www.acadvertiser.co.uk/coatbridge-airdrie-sport/lanarkshire-football/albion-rovers-fc/2012/05/02/albion-rovers-survival-hopes-hit-65864-30885627/</ref>\n\nFormer Cumnock, Thorniewood and Dunipace boss Tom - or Tam as he was better known - Spence died suddenly overnight, at the age of just 52<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pieandbovril.com/forum/index.php/topic/173664-tom-spence/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=13 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727234623/http://www.pieandbovril.com/forum/index.php/topic/173664-tom-spence/ |archive-date=27 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{NeilBrownPlayers|player1/tomspence.html}}\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|166319}}\n{{Albion Rovers F.C. managers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Spence, Tom}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:2012 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Airdrie, North Lanarkshire]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Stirling Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Alloa Athletic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Cowdenbeath F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Clydebank F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Clyde F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kilmarnock F.C. players]]\n[[Category:East Fife F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Albion Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:Scottish football managers]]\n[[Category:Albion Rovers F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League managers]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2017}}\n{{infobox football biography\n| name = Tom Spence\n\n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date|1962|01|04|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Airdrie, North Lanarkshire|Airdrie]], Scotland\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2012|04|28|1962|01|04|df=y}}\n| height = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Left-back]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = Glenboig\n| years1 = 1982\u20131988 | caps1 = 147 | goals1 = 6  | clubs1 = [[Stirling Albion F.C.|Stirling Albion]]\n| years2 = 1988      | caps2 = 1   | goals2 = 0  | clubs2 = [[Alloa Athletic F.C.|Alloa Athletic]]\n| years3 = 1988      | caps3 = 2   | goals3 = 0  | clubs3 = [[Cowdenbeath F.C.|Cowdenbeath]]\n| years4 = 1988\u20131989 | caps4 = 29  | goals4 = 4  | clubs4 = [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]]\n| years5 = 1989\u20131990 | caps5 = 12  | goals5 = 0  | clubs5 = [[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]]\n| years6 = 1990\u20131991 | caps6 = 50  | goals6 = 1  | clubs6 = [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]\n| years7 = 1991\u20131993 | caps7 = 58  | goals7 = 1  | clubs7 = [[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]]\n| years8 = 1993\u20131994 | caps8 = 12  | goals8 = 0  | clubs8 = [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]]\n| totalcaps = 311\n| totalgoals = 12\n| manageryears1 = 1994\u20131995\n| managerclubs1 = [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]]\n}}\n\n'''Tom Spence''' (4 January 1962 \u2013 28 April 2012) was a [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[association football|football]] player and [[manager (association football)|manager]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cumnockjuniorsfc.co.uk/2012/04/tom-spence/ |title=Tom Spence |publisher=Cumnock Juniors FC |date=2012-04-25 |accessdate=2012-04-29}} {{dead link|date=July 2015}}</ref>  He was born in [[Airdrie, North Lanarkshire]]. Spence played for [[Stirling Albion F.C.|Stirling Albion]], [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]], [[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]] and [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] and was captain of the Stirling Albion team which defeated [[Selkirk F.C.|Selkirk]] 20-0 in 1984.<ref>http://www.acadvertiser.co.uk/coatbridge-airdrie-sport/lanarkshire-football/albion-rovers-fc/2012/05/02/albion-rovers-survival-hopes-hit-65864-30885627/</ref>\n\nFormer Cumnock, Thorniewood and Dunipace boss Tom - or Tam as he was better known - Spence died suddenly overnight, at the age of just 52<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pieandbovril.com/forum/index.php/topic/173664-tom-spence/ |